      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The following model is a representation of aspartame, C<sub>14</sub>H<sub>18</sub>N<sub>2</sub>O<sub>5</sub>, known commercially under many names, including NutraSweet. Only the connections between atoms are shown; multiple bonds are not indicated. Complete the structure for aspartame, and indicate the positions of multiple bonds (black = C, red = O, blue = N, gray = H).</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdEFaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--6e56644cb9de087c0c38a4a11eeeffd69477b61e/OChem_01_EC_004.jpg\" alt=\"The ball and stick model of aspartame where grey, black, blue and red spheres represent hydrogen, carbon, nitrogen, and oxygen, respectively.\">",
